kexp.util.data.load_atomdata module

kexp.util.data.load_atomdata.load_atomdata(idx=0, crop_type='', path='', unshuffle_xvars=True, transpose_idx=[], average_repeats=False) → atomdata[source]

Returns the atomdata stored in the idx`th newest pickle file at `path.

Parameters:

  • idx (int) – If a positive value is specified, it is interpreted as a run_id (as stored in run_info.run_id), and that data is found and loaded. If zero or a negative number are given, data is loaded relative to the most recent dataset (idx=0).

  • path (str) – The full path to the file to be loaded. If not specified, loads the file as dictated by idx.

Returns:

ad

Return type:

atomdata
